Problem

6.1. Find the general solutions of the systems of differential equations
a) $cases(x' = x sin t, y' = x e^(cos t))$
b) $cases(x' + (2x)/t = 0, y' = (1 + 2/t)x + y)$

Problem

6.2. Find the general solutions of the differential equations
a) $(1+t^2)x'' + (x')^2 + 1 = 0$
b) $t x'' = x' ln(x'/t)$
c) $(t ln t)x'' - x' = 0$
d) $x x'' = (x')^3$
e) $1+(x')^2 = 2x x''$
f) $2x x'' + (x')^2 + (x')^4 = 0$

Problem

6.3. Find the solutions to the initial value problems
a) $ 2x x'' - 3(x')^2 = 4x^2 $, $ x(0)=1 $, $x'(0)=0$
b) $ 3x' x'' = e^x $, $ x(-3)=0 $, $x'(-3)=1$

Problem

6.4. Find the equation of motion of a freely falling body of mass $m$, taking into account the air resistance expressed by the formula $ G = k v^2 $, where $k$ is a positive constant and $v$ is the velocity of motion. Find the solution to this equation.

Problem

6.5. Find the general solution of the differential equation
$t^2 x x'' = (x - t x')^2$

Problem

6.6. Find the solution to the initial value problem
$cases(x' = y, y' = y^2 / x) $$ cases(x(0) = 1, y(0) = 2) $

Problem

6.7. Find the solution to the initial value problem
$cases(x' = 1 - 1/y, y' = 1 / (x - t)) $$ cases(x(0) = -1, y(0) = 1) $
